# Typography System

The typography system lives in `app/style/type.scss` and is auto-loaded via `nuxt.config.ts`. Use the system — do not invent ad-hoc `font-family` or sizing.

## Font families

Three custom local fonts are loaded via `@font-face`. Apply them with mixins or utility classes — never with a raw `font-family` string.

| Mixin           | Utility class | Underlying `font-family` |
| --------------- | ------------- | ------------------------ |
| `@include sans` | `.sans`       | `"sans"` (variable, weight 1–999) |
| `@include thin` | `.thin`       | `"thin"`                          |
| `@include italic` | `.italic`   | `"italic"` (variable, weight 1–999) |

There is also a CSS variable `--system-font` for system-font fallbacks (used in `body`).

```scss
// correct
.label {
  @include sans;
  font-weight: 450;
}

// wrong - raw font stack
.label {
  font-family: "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif;
}
```

## Heading and body scale

`h1`–`h6`, `p`, and `small` are already styled in `type.scss` with fluid `clamp()` sizing and the appropriate mixin. Use the right semantic tag; avoid overriding `font-size` / `line-height` / `font-family` on them without a strong reason.

```vue
<!-- preferred: let the global scale do the work -->
<h2>Section heading</h2>
<p>Body copy…</p>
```

## Text utility classes

These ship globally from `type.scss`:

- `.sans`, `.thin`, `.italic` — apply a font family
- `.uc` — `text-transform: uppercase`
- `.tac` / `.tar` / `.taj` — text-align center / right / justify
- `.underline` — `text-decoration: underline`

## Global CSS variables for styling

From `reset.scss`:

- `--unit: 1.2rem` — base spacing unit
- `--max-width: 200rem`
- `--ease`, `--ease-qubic`, `--spring` — easing tokens
- `--zmax`, `--z5` … `--z0`, `--zmin` — z-index scale

Prefer these tokens over hard-coded values where they fit.
